file.name: openapi.yml
file.content:
openapi: 3.0.1
info:
  x-ballerina-display:
    label: Shipwire Receivings
    iconPath: "icon.png"
  title: Shipwire Receivings API
  description: |
    This is a generated connector for [Shipwire Receivings API v3.0](https://www.shipwire.com/developers/receiving) OpenAPI specification.
    Allows managing inventory at Shipwire and Shipwire Anywhere warehouses using receiving orders.
  x-ballerina-init-description: >
    The connector initialization requires setting the API credentials. 
  
    Create a [Shipwire account](https://www.shipwire.com) and obtain tokens by following [this guide](https://www.shipwire.com/developers/getting-started).
  version: "3.0"
servers:
- url: https://api.shipwire.com/
security:
- basicAuth: []
paths:
  /api/v3/receivings:
    get:
      tags:
      - Receivings
      summary: Get list of advance ship notices
      description: Get an itemized list of receivings.
      operationId: GetReceivings
      parameters:
      - name: expand
        in: query
        description: Expand receivings data in the response, instead of accessing
          directly via a URL (comma separated list). See resources `Holds`, `Instruction
          Recipients`, `Items`, `Shipments`, `labels` and `Trackings` for information
          on the data model returned by this parameter.
        style: form
        explode: true
        schema:
          type: array
          items:
            type: string
            format: enum
            enum:
            - holds
            - instructionsRecipients
            - items
            - shipments
            - labels
            - trackings
            - all
      - name: commerceName
        in: query
        description: Filter by commerceName (comma separated list)
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: transactionId
        in: query
        description: Filter by transactionId (comma separated list)
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: externalId
        in: query
        description: Filter by externalId (comma separated list)
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: orderId
        in: query
        description: Filter by orderId (comma separated list)
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: orderNo
        in: query
        description: Filter by orderNo (comma separated list)
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: status
        in: query
        description: Filter by status (comma separated list)
        schema:
          type: string
          format: enum
          enum:
          - processed
          - canceled
          - completed
          - delivered
          - returned
          - submitted
          - held
          - tracked
      - name: updatedAfter
        in: query
        description: 'Only show resources updated after this date (ISO 8601 format,
          ex: "2014-05-30T13:08:29-07:00")'
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: warehouseId
        in: query
        description: Filter by warehouseId (comma separated list)
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: warehouseExternalId
        in: query
        description: Filter by warehouseExternalId (comma separated list)
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: vendorId
        in: query
        description: Filter by vendorId
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: vendorExternalId
        in: query
        description: Filter by vendorExternalId
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetListOfAdvanceShipNoticesResponse'
    post:
      tags:
      - Receivings
      summary: Create an advance ship notice
      description: Create a new receiving.
      operationId: PostReceivings
      parameters:
      - name: expand
        in: query
        description: Expand receivings data in the response, instead of accessing
          directly via a URL (comma separated list). See resources `Holds`, `Instruction
          Recipients`, `Items`, `Shipments`, `labels` and `Trackings` for information
          on the data model returned by this parameter.
        style: form
        explode: true
        schema:
          type: array
          items:
            type: string
            format: enum
            enum:
            - holds
            - instructionsRecipients
            - items
            - shipments
            - labels
            - trackings
            - all
      requestBody:
        description: CreateAnAdvanceShipNotice request
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/CreateAnAdvanceShipNoticeRequest'
        required: true
      responses:
        200:
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/PostListOfAdvanceShipNoticesResponse'
      x-codegen-request-body-name: body
  /api/v3/receivings/{id}:
    get:
      tags:
      - Receivings
      summary: Get advance ship notice
      description: Get information about this receiving.
      operationId: GetReceivingsById
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: The advance ship notice's ID.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: expand
        in: query
        description: Expand receivings data in the response, instead of accessing
          directly via a URL (comma separated list). See resources `Holds`, `Instruction
          Recipients`, `Items`, `Shipments`, `labels` and `Trackings` for information
          on the data model returned by this parameter.
        style: form
        explode: true
        schema:
          type: array
          items:
            type: string
            format: enum
            enum:
            - holds
            - instructionsRecipients
            - items
            - shipments
            - labels
            - trackings
            - all
      responses:
        200:
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetAdvanceShipNoticeResponse'
    put:
      tags:
      - Receivings
      summary: Update an advance ship notice
      description: Modify information about this receiving.
      operationId: PutReceivingsById
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: The advance ship notice's ID.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: expand
        in: query
        description: Expand receivings data in the response, instead of accessing
          directly via a URL (comma separated list). See resources `Holds`, `Instruction
          Recipients`, `Items`, `Shipments`, `labels` and `Trackings` for information
          on the data model returned by this parameter.
        style: form
        explode: true
        schema:
          type: array
          items:
            type: string
            format: enum
            enum:
            - holds
            - instructionsRecipients
            - items
            - shipments
            - labels
            - trackings
            - all
      requestBody:
        description: CreateAnAdvanceShipNotice request
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: '#/components/schemas/CreateAnAdvanceShipNoticeRequest'
        required: true
      responses:
        200:
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetAdvanceShipNoticeResponse'
      x-codegen-request-body-name: body
  /api/v3/receivings/{id}/cancel:
    post:
      tags:
      - Receivings
      summary: Cancel a receiving order
      description: Cancel this receiving.
      operationId: PostReceivingsCancelById
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: The advance ship notice's ID.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/CancelAReceivingOrderResponse'
  /api/v3/receivings/{id}/labels/cancel:
    post:
      tags:
      - Receivings
      summary: Cancel a receiving label
      description: Cancel shipping labels on this receiving.
      operationId: PostReceivingsLabelsCancelById
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: The advance ship notice's ID.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/CancelAReceivingLabelResponse'
  /api/v3/receivings/{id}/holds:
    get:
      tags:
      - Receivings
      summary: Get holds detail
      description: Get the list of holds, if any, on this receiving.
      operationId: GetReceivingsHoldsById
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: The advance ship notice's ID.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      - name: includeCleared
        in: query
        description: When set to 1, response includes holds that have been cleared.
        schema:
          type: integer
          enum:
          - 0
          - 1
      responses:
        200:
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetHoldDetailsResponse'
  /api/v3/receivings/{id}/instructionsRecipients:
    get:
      tags:
      - Receivings
      summary: Get instructions and the recipients contact details
      description: Get instructions and email recipients for this receiving.
      operationId: GetReceivingsInstructionsRecipientsById
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: The advance ship notice's ID.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetInstructionsRecipientsDetailsResponse'
  /api/v3/receivings/{id}/extendedAttributes:
    get:
      tags:
      - Receivings
      summary: Get receiving extended attributes
      description: Get the extended attributes of this receiving.
      operationId: GetReceivingsExtendedAttributesById
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: The receiving's ID.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetReceivingExtendedAttributesResponse'
  /api/v3/receivings/{id}/items:
    get:
      tags:
      - Receivings
      summary: Get items detail
      description: Get the contents of this receiving.
      operationId: GetReceivingsItemsById
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: The advance ship notice's ID.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetItemsDetailResponse'
  /api/v3/receivings/{id}/shipments:
    get:
      tags:
      - Receivings
      summary: Get shipment details
      description: Get shipping dimension and container information.
      operationId: GetReceivingsShipmentsById
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: The advance ship notice's ID.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetShipmentDetailsResponse'
  /api/v3/receivings/{id}/trackings:
    get:
      tags:
      - Receivings
      summary: Get trackings detail
      description: Get tracking information for this receiving.
      operationId: GetReceivingsTrackingsById
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: The advance ship notice's ID.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetTrackingsDetailResponse'
  /api/v3/receivings/{id}/labels:
    get:
      tags:
      - Receivings
      summary: Get labels detail
      description: |-
        Get labels information for this receiving.
        To retrieve the labels as PDF add the following header to the request:
        Accept: application/pdf
      operationId: GetReceivingsLabelsById
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: The advance ship notice's ID.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetLabelsDetailResponse'
            application/pdf:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/GetLabelsDetailResponse'
  /api/v3.1/receivings/{id}/markComplete:
    post:
      tags:
      - Receivings
      summary: Mark the receiving completed
      description: Mark this receiving order as complete. This endpoint works only
        for Shipwire Anywhere warehouses.
      operationId: PostReceivingsMarkCompleteById
      parameters:
      - name: id
        in: path
        description: The advance ship notice's ID.
        required: true
        schema:
          type: string
      responses:
        200:
          description: OK
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/MarkTheReceivingCompletedResponse'
components:
  schemas:
    ReceivingServerResponse:
      title: Receiving Server Response
      type: object
      properties:
        status:
          type: integer
          description: This is the HTTP status code.
          example: 200
        message:
          type: string
          description: This is the HTTP status message.
          example: Successful
        resourceLocation:
          type: string
          description: A URL that gives more information about the linked resource.
            A 'null' value would mean that no further information is available for
            that resource.
          example: https://api.shipwire.com/api/v3/receivings?offset=0&limit=20&expand=all
      description: Receiving Server Response
    ExtendedAttributes:
      type: object
      description: Extended attributes
      properties:
        name:
          type: string
          description: Name of the extended attribute i.e. any additional information
            as per the customer request to be added in the receiving order. (e.g.
            return instructions)
          example: returnInstruction
        value:
          type: string
          description: Value of the extended attribute which depends on the customer
            request. (e.g. For return instructions the value can be mail in or store)
          example: Mail in or store
        type:
          type: string
          description: Data type of the extended attribute value i.e. a string or
            integer
          example: string
    ReceivingHold:
      title: Holds on Advance ship notice
      type: object
      properties:
        id:
          type: integer
          description: This is the unique ID assigned to a particular hold in the
            shipwire system.
          example: 51
        orderId:
          type: integer
          description: This is the receving order ID in the shipwire system on which
            the hold is applied.
          example: 8411
        externalOrderId:
          maxLength: 32
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is the receving order ID in the external system on which
            the hold is applied.
          example: OM10001
        type:
          maxLength: 100
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is the type of hold due to which the order is stuck. (e.g.
            customer, admin, etc.)
          example: customer
        description:
          maxLength: 255
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is the description given for the hold in the Shipwire
            system.
          example: Please edit your ASN and accept the  Packing List acknowledgement,
            High Value Items acknowledgement.
        appliedDate:
          type: string
          description: This is the date on which the hold is applied to the order.
          format: date-time
          example: 2018-05-27T00:00:00-07:00
        clearedDate:
          type: string
          description: This is the date on which the hold is removed from the order.
          format: date-time
          example: 2018-05-28T00:00:00-07:00
      description: Holds that apply to this advance ship notice
    ReceivingHolds:
      type: object
      properties:
        resourceLocation:
          type: string
          description: A URL that gives more information about the linked resource.
            A 'null' value would mean that no further information is available for
            that resource.
          example: https://api.developer.shipwire.com/api/v3/receivings/8411/holds?expand=all&offset=0&limit=20
        resource:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/ReceivingHolds_resource'
    ReceivingLotControl:
      type: object
      properties:
        lotId:
          type: string
          description: A unique ID assigned to a particular quantity or lot of material
            shipped from a siingle merchant.
          example: hgf897
        quantity:
          type: integer
          description: The  quantity of total SKU items belonging to the particular
            lot.
          example: 10
        expirationDate:
          type: string
          description: This is the expiry date of the product belonging to the particular
            lot.
          format: date-time
          example: 2018-05-28T00:00:00-07:00
    CreateReceivingItem:
      title: Receiving Item
      type: object
      properties:
        sku:
          maxLength: 50
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: SKU (Stock Keeping Unit) is a unique name for your product
            and is required for both physical and virtual products in inventory.
          example: T-shirt
        quantity:
          type: integer
          description: The  quantity of total SKU items belonging to the particular
            lot.
          example: 10
        id:
          type: integer
          description: A unique auto-generated ID assigned to each new line item added
            to the Shipwire Platform.
          example: 1
        productId:
          type: integer
          description: A unique auto-generated ID assigned to each new product added
            to the Shipwire Product Catalog.
        productExternalId:
          maxLength: 50
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: A unique user-provided identifier for a product in an external
            system.
          example: ORDDET0001
        orderId:
          type: integer
          description: This is the receving order ID in the shipwire system on which
            the hold is applied.
          example: 213
        orderExternalId:
          maxLength: 32
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is the receving order ID in the external system on which
            the hold is applied.
          example: ORD0001
        expected:
          type: integer
          description: The total number of SKU items expected to be received at the
            warehouse as per the order.
          example: 2
        pending:
          type: integer
          description: The number of pending SKU items expected to be received at
            the warehouse.
          example: 2
        good:
          type: integer
          description: The number of SKU items ready for fulfillment in the warehouse.
          example: 2
        inReview:
          type: integer
          description: The number of SKU items currently under review within the warehouse.
            (i.e. items being reviewed to determine if they are in sellable condition
            or damaged, etc.)
          example: 2
        damaged:
          type: integer
          description: The number of SKU items found to be damaged (during receiving
            or otherwise) within the warehouse and unavailable for fulfillment.
          example: 2
      description: Item being shipped to Shipwire
    ReceivingItem:
      title: Receiving Item
      type: object
      properties:
        sku:
          maxLength: 50
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: SKU (Stock Keeping Unit) is a unique name for your product
            and is required for both physical and virtual products in inventory.
          example: T-shirt
        quantity:
          type: integer
          description: The  quantity of total SKU items belonging to the particular
            lot.
          example: 10
        id:
          type: integer
          description: A unique auto-generated ID assigned to each new line item added
            to the Shipwire Platform.
          example: 1
        productId:
          type: integer
          description: A unique auto-generated ID assigned to each new product added
            to the Shipwire Product Catalog.
        productExternalId:
          maxLength: 50
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: A unique user-provided identifier for a product in an external
            system.
          example: ORDDET0001
        orderId:
          type: integer
          description: This is the receving order ID in the shipwire system on which
            the hold is applied.
          example: 213
        orderExternalId:
          maxLength: 32
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is the receving order ID in the external system on which
            the hold is applied.
          example: ORD0001
        expected:
          type: integer
          description: The total number of SKU items expected to be received at the
            warehouse as per the order.
          example: 2
        pending:
          type: integer
          description: The number of pending SKU items expected to be received at
            the warehouse.
          example: 2
        good:
          type: integer
          description: The number of SKU items ready for fulfillment in the warehouse.
          example: 2
        inReview:
          type: integer
          description: The number of SKU items currently under review within the warehouse.
            (i.e. items being reviewed to determine if they are in sellable condition
            or damaged, etc.)
          example: 2
        damaged:
          type: integer
          description: The number of SKU items found to be damaged (during receiving
            or otherwise) within the warehouse and unavailable for fulfillment.
          example: 2
        lotControl:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/ReceivingItem_lotControl'
        extendedAttributes:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/ReceivingItem_extendedAttributes'
      description: Item being shipped to Shipwire
    ReceivingItems:
      title: Receiving Items
      type: object
      properties:
        resourceLocation:
          type: string
          description: A URL that gives more information about the linked resource.
            A 'null' value would mean that no further information is available for
            that resource.
          example: https://api.shipwire.com/api/v3/receivings/8411/items?expand=all&offset=0&limit=20
        resource:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/ReceivingItems_resource'
      description: Items being shipped to Shipwire
    Tracking:
      type: object
      properties:
        id:
          type: integer
          description: This is the unquie ID generated in the shipwire system for
            each tracking record.
          example: 1
        orderId:
          type: integer
          description: This is the receving order ID in the shipwire system on which
            the hold is applied.
          example: 8411
        orderExternalId:
          maxLength: 32
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is the receving order ID in the external system on which
            the hold is applied.
          example: ORD0001
        tracking:
          maxLength: 50
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is reference tracking number provided by the carrier for
            tracking purposes.
          example: TRACK0001
        carrier:
          maxLength: 50
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is the unique ID of the carrier used to deliver the order
            to the warehouse.
          example: CAR00111
        contact:
          maxLength: 50
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: Name of person from the carrier company who can be contacted
            for any communication.
          example: Andrew Carr
        phone:
          maxLength: 50
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: Phone number of the contact person from the carrier company
            for any communication.
          example: "78872837827"
        url:
          type: string
          description: A URL that gives more information about the tracking record.
          example: null
        summary:
          type: string
          description: Summary added to the tracking record for tracking purposes.
          example: null
        summaryDate:
          type: string
          description: Date on which the summary is added to the tracking record.
          format: date-time
          example: 2018-05-27T00:00:00-07:00
        trackedDate:
          type: string
          format: date-time
          example: 2018-05-27T00:00:00-07:00
        delivered1Date:
          type: string
          description: Date on which the the inventory is received against the tracking
            record.
          format: date-time
          example: 2014-05-27T00:00:00-07:00
        firstScanDate:
          type: string
          description: Date the order's associated shipping carrier scans the label
            when it receives the order.
          format: date-time
          example: 2018-05-26T00:00:00-07:00
        labelCreationDate:
          type: string
          description: Date on which the shipping labels are created for the tracking
            record.
          format: date-time
          example: 2018-05-26T00:00:00-07:00
    Trackings:
      type: object
      properties:
        resource:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/Trackings_resource'
        resourceLocation:
          type: string
          description: A URL that gives more information about the linked resource.
            A 'null' value would mean that no further information is available for
            that resource.
          example: https://api.shipwire.com/api/v3/receivings/8411/trackings?offset=0&limit=20&expand=all
      description: Specifies shipment tracking details. See `trackings` resource.
    Shipment:
      type: object
      description: Shipment
      properties:
        shipmentId:
          type: integer
          description: A unique ID assigned to the shipment (container) in the shipwire
            system.
          example: 12
        type:
          type: string
          description: Type of the shipment (container) based on the contents stored
            in it (e.g. a box, parcel, etc.)
          example: box
        height:
          type: number
          description: This is the height of the shipment (container) based on its
            Unit of Measurement
          format: decimal
          example: 12.0
        length:
          type: number
          description: This is the length of the shipment (container) based on its
            Unit of Measurement
          format: decimal
          example: 2.99
        weight:
          type: number
          description: This is the weight of the shipment (container) based on its
            Unit of Measurement
          format: decimal
          example: 1.2
        width:
          type: number
          description: This is the width of the shipment (container) based on its
            Unit of Measurement
          format: decimal
          example: 12.0
    Shipments:
      type: object
      properties:
        resource:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/Shipments_resource'
        resourceLocation:
          type: string
          description: A URL that gives more information about the linked resource.
            A 'null' value would mean that no further information is available for
            that resource.
          example: https://api.shipwire.com/api/v3/receivings/673/trackings?offset=0&limit=20&expand=all
      description: Specifies goods details. See `shipment` resource.
    Label:
      type: object
      properties:
        labelId:
          type: integer
          description: A unique ID assigned to each shipping label in the shipwire
            system.
          example: 1
        orderId:
          type: integer
          description: This is the receving order ID in the shipwire system on which
            the hold is applied.
          example: 8411
        orderExternalId:
          maxLength: 32
          minLength: 1
          type: string
          description: This is the receving order ID in the external system on which
            the hold is applied.
          example: ORD00101
    Labels:
      type: object
      properties:
        resource:
          $ref: '#/components/schemas/Labels_resource'
        resourceLocation:

          type: string
